## Zeta Atlas Workflow

Purpose: build a strategic, queryable map of Bloomberg articles before deep extraction.

### Steps
1) Select sitemap:
   - Fresh news: `news/latest.xml`
   - Archive month: `news/YYYY-MM.xml`
   - Section fronts: `collections/sectionfronts.xml`
   - Ticker mapping: `securities/index.xml` shards

2) Run Cartographer with filters:
```bash
./zeta_agents/13_cartographer_agent.js <SITEMAP_URL> \
  --include=earnings,fed,cpi \
  --exclude=politics,opinion \
  --tickers=nvda,aapl \
  --since-days=7 \
  --limit=25
```

3) Review `zeta_atlas.json` (contains `{ url, lastmod, category }`).

4) Feed selected URLs into Predator/Diffbot or direct-strike + Zeta Brain for article-level synthesis.

### Files
- Cartographer: [zeta_agents/13_cartographer_agent.js](mdc:zeta_agents/13_cartographer_agent.js)
- Brain: [zeta_missions/4_intelligence_synthesis.js](mdc:zeta_missions/4_intelligence_synthesis.js)

### Best Practices
- Always pre-filter aggressively to minimize LLM usage
- Favor `news/latest.xml` for recency-sensitive missions
- Use securities sitemap to construct per-ticker target lists

